This article is a Presidential Memorandum issued by President Barack Obama in 2010. The memorandum establishes a Task Force on Childhood Obesity with the goal of solving the problem of childhood obesity within a generation. The Task Force consists of various members from executive departments and agencies, with the Assistant to the President for Domestic Policy serving as the Chair. The Task Force is directed to develop an interagency action plan to address childhood obesity and make recommendations in areas such as ensuring access to healthy food, increasing physical activity, providing healthier food in schools, and empowering parents with information and tools. The memorandum also emphasizes the need for collaboration with other public and non-governmental actors and conducting outreach to private and nonprofit organizations. The memorandum concludes with general provisions and instructions for publication.